article_id:1868,category_name:Events,title_name:A New Raid Event, Cursed Connections, Is Now Live!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/9709c57bafa1d6b5699cfdf16a569c98.png,message:<div>Up to four players with four adventurers each (up to 16 adventurers in total!) can battle together in the Cursed Connections raid event, which began <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1609394400"></span>. Take on event-specific quests to defeat the wind-attuned raid boss and earn rewards!</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/9709c57bafa1d6b5699cfdf16a569c98.png"></div><div>The Prince and friends prepare the greet the new year in the Hinomotoan style, as has been their tradition for years. This peaceful period of reflection and celebration is shattered by the sudden appearance of a stranger named Doman who somehow manages to wrest control of the Halidom away from our heroes. The Prince joins forces with Seimei, the leader of the Ox Wyrmclan, to take back his home from this usurper, but it soon becomes clear that the connection between Seimei and Doman is more complicated than it first appears. To get the new year off to a good start, the Prince will have to clash with the mysterious Mukuroshu as they put their sinister schemes into action!<br><br>Event theme song: &quot;Terrestrial paradise&quot; by BlooDye　<br><br>An adventurer, Kuzunoha, will join you during this event. Increase your friendship with her to add her to your roster permanently. You can also use collected blazons and emblems to get Kuzunoha&#39;s Convictions and use them to upgrade Kuzunoha&#39;s mana circles.<br><br>■Event Duration<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1609394400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1610517599"></span><br>・If the event ends while you are in a quest, the quest will continue until the results have been determined. You will be able to earn rewards according to the results of the quest.<br><br>■Reward Availability Period<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1609394400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1611122399"></span><br>・You will be able to perform blazon summons and obtain emblem rewards during this period.<br><br>■Story and Omega Difficulty Unlock<br>Episode four of the story and Omega difficulty will unlock at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1609999200"></span>.<br>・Omega difficulty will not appear until the above date and time.<br><br>■Epilogue<br>The epilogue will unlock at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1610517600"></span>.<br>・To view the epilogue, you must complete episode 5 of the event story.<br><br>■Epilogue Availability<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1610517600"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1611122399"></span><br><br>■Temporary Adventurers<br>When you complete quests, you will increase the friendship with any temporary adventurers in your team. If you maximize your friendship with a temporary adventurer, they will permanently remain in your collection, allowing you to include them in your team after the event ends. Their level, stats, equipment, and position in your team and collection will be maintained.<br>・Even if an event adventurer isn&#39;t permanently added to your collection, any items used to upgrade their level or unlock their mana circles will not be returned.<br><br>・Event adventurer upgrade item<br>In this event you can earn up to 54 Kuzunoha&#39;s Convictions, an item used to upgrade the temporary adventurer Kuzunoha, from emblem rewards, blazon summoning, and limited-time endeavors.<br><br>You can use event adventurer upgrade items earned in this event on the mana circles of temporary adventurers who join you in this event to unlock nodes or unbind new mana circles.<br><br>Until the epilogue availability period for this event ends, you can only unlock nodes or unbind new mana circles of temporary adventurers who join you in this event by using event adventurer upgrade items earned in this event.<br><br>Once the epilogue availability period for this event has ended, if you do not have any event adventurer upgrade items to unlock mana nodes or unbind new mana circles, then you can use materials and mana instead.<br><br>・Event perks<br>While this event is active, the temporary adventurer will have special abilities that activate in quests for this event. See Event Perks on the main event screen in-game for more information.<br><br>■Raid Battles<br>Raid battles are co-op battles where up to four teams (16 adventurers) can cooperate against a raid boss together! To participate in a raid battle, you must either create a room as the host or join a room as a guest.<br><br>・As a Host:<br>Creating a room requires otherworld fragments and getherwings.<br>You can obtain otherworld fragments from boss battles.<br><br>・As a Guest:<br>Joining a room requires otherworld fragments and getherwings.<br>You must have unlocked the respective difficulty to participate in a raid battle.<br><br>■Extra Raid Battles<br>There will be no Extra Raid Battles for this event.<br><br>■Match with a Mischief-Maker<br>A quest that can only be completed solo and is unlocked when you clear an expert Raid Battle. You can get a large number of each emblem as well as blazons by clearing this quest.<br><br>Fried tofu items are required to challenge the Match with a Mischief-Maker quest. You can earn fried tofu as endeavor rewards or as part of a Grand Bounty.<br><br>Note: Match with a Mischief-Maker does not consume stamina.<br><br>■Omega Difficulty<br><br>Omega Difficulty will be unlocked at the below time:<br><br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1609999200"></span><br><br>To challenge Omega difficulty, you must clear the raid battle on Nightmare difficulty as well as episode 5 of the story. Additionally, to unlock Omega difficulty, you must collect three omega keys. You can obtain one omega key from each type of emblem rewards: bronze emblems, silver emblems, and gold emblems.<br><br>・Omega Level 1 (Solo)<br>This quest is for solo play only.<br>It will unlock when you clear the raid battle on Nightmare difficulty as well as episode 5 of the story.<br><br>・Omega Level 1 (Raid)<br>This quest is for co-op play only.<br>It will unlock when you clear the Omega battle Level 1 in solo play.<br><br>・Omega Level 2 (Solo)<br>This quest is for solo play only.<br>It will unlock when you clear the Omega battle Level 1 in co-op play.<br><br>・Omega Level 2 (Raid)<br>This quest is for co-op play only.<br>It will unlock when you clear the Omega battle Level 2 &nbsp;in solo play.<br><br>・Omega Level 3 (Solo)<br>This quest is for solo play only.<br>It will unlock when you clear the Omega battle Level 2 in co-op play.<br><br>・Omega Level 3 (Raid)<br>This quest is for co-op play only.<br>It will unlock when you clear the Omega battle Level 3 in solo play.<br><br>■Raid Boosts<br>When you clear raid battles, you&#39;ll be able to get raid boosts, which power up adventurers for this event only.<br><br>Raid boosts you obtain will stack, and only apply to your team. The maximum effects you can achieve with raid boosts are described below.<br>・Damage +100%<br>・HP +50%<br>・Shapeshift Prep +25%<br>・Dragon Time +50%<br><br>The number of raid boosts you can obtain by clearing a single quest varies depending on the difficulty. There are also special rare raid boosts.<br>・In this event, you will not be able to obtain rare raid boosts from boss battles.<br><br>Raid battle co-op rooms will display each team&#39;s boosted might, which factors in the increased power from raid boosts.<br>・Boosted might does not affect the might required to start a quest.<br><br>■Blazon Summons<br>Complete boss battles and raid battles to obtain peregrine blazons. Blazons collected can be used for blazon summoning to get Kuzunoha&#39;s Convictions and other rewards.<br><br>After obtaining a Kuzunoha&#39;s Conviction, you can reset the contents available. From the 5th reset onward, you must accept all rewards before you can reset the contents available.<br><br>■Emblems<br>You can obtain rewards, such as Kuzunoha&#39;s Convictions, based on the total number of emblems you gather during the event.<br><br>■Event Endeavors<br>Two types of event endeavors will be available during the event: Daily and Limited.<br><br>Notes:<br>1. During raid battles, you will only recover 1/4 of the amount of HP from certain skills and abilities.<br>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to participate in event quests.<br>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to play co-op.<br>4. If you do not maximize your friendship with temporary adventurers during the event, they will not join you after the event ends, regardless of their level or stats.<br>5. If a temporary adventurer permanently joins your roster, you will be able to read their Adventurer Story.<br>6. You will not be able to use blazons, emblems, fried tofu, or otherworld fragments obtained in this event in future events.<br>7. For details concerning this raid event, check the Help section on the raid event&#39;s top page in the game.<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1609394400,update_time1609384784